    "instruction": "Load trace.csv and compute global P95 per (cmdb_id, trace_name) using the full trace.csv. Parse timestamp as pd.to_datetime(..., unit='s', utc=True). Define incident window start='2024-01-20T04:36:00Z' end='2024-01-20T05:06:00Z'. Filter trace.csv to rows with cmdb_id in [\"checkoutservice\",\"currencyservice\",\"emailservice\",\"productcatalogservice\",\"recommendationservice\"] and timestamp within the incident window. For each (cmdb_id, trace_name) group compute: count_in_window, anomaly_count = number of in-window points with value >= global P95, earliest_anom_ts (ISO UTC) or NaN, max_value_in_window, p95_global, ratio = max_value_in_window / p95_global (handle p95==0 explicitly). Return a compact table of up to top 20 rows sorted by anomaly_count desc. Also return (separately) all trace rows in-window for cmdb_id=='emailservice' where trace_name contains any of ['error_rate','duration_p95','duration_mean','row_count'] (limit to top 50 rows) with timestamps as ISO UTC strings."}

