    "analysis": "We ran trace-level aggregates and inspected emailservice traces. Findings: many trace \"error_rate\" groups have global p95 == 0 (artifacts) producing infinite ratios and are not trustworthy as direct root-cause signals. Trace-level non-trivial anomalies (p95>0 and ratio>1) are scarce. From metric-level analysis the strongest meaningful signal is emailservice latency-50 (ratio ≈ 1.20) with earliest anomaly at 2024-01-20T04:51:00Z; several other services show modest CPU/latency/workload exceedances (~5–7%). Logs aggregated earlier showed log.error_count == 0 for services, and error_logs aggregation was empty. To proceed with fault identification and root-cause localization we should (1) identify fault segments (consecutive anomalies) for the meaningful metric signals — starting with emailservice — and (2) then cross-check with traces and logs. The next atomic step is to perform metric-level fault identification for emailservice (and optionally other top non-trivial metric candidates) to get exact fault start/end times and severity.",
